        <h2 id="verdict">Is Moz Pro worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For first-time SEO subscribers: yes.</strong> The 30-day free trial is unbeatable, the UI is beginner-friendly, and Domain Authority is still the most quoted metric in SEO reports. Moz Pro is a smart starting point.</p>

        <p><strong>For power users: no.</strong> Ahrefs has a fresher index and deeper SERP data. Semrush has more tools (50+ vs Moz's ~10) plus PPC and social. The on-page grader trails Surfer and Clearscope. If you have outgrown beginner SEO, you have outgrown Moz Pro.</p>

        <p><strong>For business owners without writers: no.</strong> Moz Pro shows you opportunities but cannot execute on them. Real cost to actually publish content with Moz data lands at $2,500–$5,000/mo. A done-for-you platform ships finished articles for the price of the Moz subscription alone.</p>

