        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is Moz Pro?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Moz Pro is an all-in-one SEO platform founded by Rand Fishkin and Gillian Muessig in 2004 (originally SEOmoz). It serves 40,000+ customers worldwide and is now part of Ziff Davis. It pioneered the Domain Authority metric and bundles keyword research, link analysis, site audit, and rank tracking.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How much does Moz Pro cost in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Standard $99/mo, Medium $179/mo, Large $249/mo, Premium $299/mo. Annual billing saves 20%. There is a 30-day free trial — the most generous in the SEO suite category.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is Domain Authority?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Domain Authority (DA) is Moz's proprietary 1–100 score predicting how likely a domain is to rank in Google SERPs. It is based on the size and quality of the backlink profile and remains the most widely cited link-strength metric outside Ahrefs Domain Rating.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Moz Pro vs Ahrefs — which is better?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Ahrefs has the larger and fresher backlink index plus a cleaner UI. Moz is easier for beginners, has a 30-day free trial, and offers MozLocal for local SEO. Pick Ahrefs for professional backlink work; pick Moz for first-time SEO subscribers and local-heavy businesses.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Does Moz Pro write content?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Moz Pro has a basic on-page grader that scores existing content against a target keyword, but it does not write, draft, or publish anything. Writers and a publishing workflow are still required.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Is Moz Pro worth $99/mo in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For beginners and small in-house SEO teams — yes, especially given the 30-day free trial. For power users — Ahrefs or Semrush offer more depth. For business owners needing content — no; the real cost to actually run SEO with Moz lands around $5,000/mo.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Does Moz Pro have local SEO?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Limited. The base Moz Pro plan has minor local features; MozLocal is sold separately as an add-on that handles citations and listing management. It is not a full Google Business Profile platform.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is the best Moz Pro alternative?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For backlink-first research: Ahrefs ($129/mo). For all-in-one SEO + PPC: Semrush ($139/mo). For budget keyword work: Mangools ($49/mo). For done-for-you content publishing: theStacc ($99/mo).</p></div></div></div>
